<section>
    <div class="container">   
            <p>If you are a student interested in applying for one of the semester exchange programs, you must first meet with Sandra Tabert in the Undergraduate Academic Advising office. Please visit the COBA Pass website and schedule an appointment to meet with her directly. Afterwards, you will be required to log in to the UCF Study Abroad Online System and fill out the application by the deadline date posted for the program that you are interested in. You must also fill out the "Essay" section of the application, but will not be required to fill out the "References" section. The International Business Study Abroad Committee will meet after the posted deadline for review and selection. Once all seats are taken, additional applicants will be placed on a waiting list.</p> 
            The Semester Exchange programs for undergraduate business students are carried out with UCF partner schools. All partner schools hold both regional, and AACSB and/or EQUIS business school accreditation. UCF students must pay UCF tuition, living expenses, and for their travel. Participants can use financial aid, scholarships, and student loans to help cover the cost of these programs. Students must be accepted into a specific program before being allowed to register for classes. UCF students must be registered for at least 12 credit hours during their semester abroad
            <p>College of Business Administration students in The Burnett Honors College have the ability to apply for the IB Scholarship that is sponsored by the College of Business Administration and the Honors College. If you are an Honors student, please make sure to apply for the IB Scholarship before the deadline date in order to be eligible for the scholarship. Contact Sandra Tabert or Nicole Gelfert for more information on scholarships available to Honors students.</p> 
            <p>For more information on financial aid, including grants, loans and scholarships, please meet with Ric Colon in the Office of Student Financial Assistance in Millican Hall, Room 120, or send him an email.</p> 
            <h3>Eligibility Requirements:</h3>
                            
            <ol>
                <li>Business major</li>
                <li>Business Common Program Prerequisites complete</li>
            <li>Earned a cumulative GPA of at least a 3.0 at UCF</li>
            <li>Satisfied all necessary prerequisites prior to the study abroad term</li>
            <li>Has attended UCF for at least two full semesters prior to the beginning of the semester abroad</li>
            <li>You must have at least one semester left to graduate, upon returning from your semester abroad.</li>
            </ol>
                            
                     
            <h3>Business Exchange Programs</h3>
