            <p>Short-term study abroad programs are often offered over the Summer, but can also be take place during Spring Break or Winter Break. They are ideal for students with limited time and resources who still want to experience multi-cultural interaction and intellectual growth. Short-term programs offer students the opportunity to immerse themselves in aspects of another culture—the language, literature, history, art and archaeology—as well as have the opportunity to live abroad.</p>
            <p>If you are interested in applying for one of the short-term study abroad programs, you must first meet with Sandra Tabert in the Undergraduate Academic Advising office. Students will be required to log in to the UCF Study Abroad Online System to apply for the programs. Applications and information about program fees and payment deadlines are handled by the UCF Office of International Studies.</p>
